his building are a product of HU’s technology accelerator and incubator focus,” said HU President Eric Darr."},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"text","text":"For decades, the 4,500-square-foot brick building housed the Martz Hardware store, but has been vacant for about 30 years as the area fell into dilapidation. The redevelopment was undertaken by local developer Mayur Patel."},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"text","text":"“This city is open for business,” said Brad Jones, CEO of Harristown Enterprises, which has redeveloped surrounding blocks. “There’s one exciting project after another, and there are many more ribbon-cuttings to come.”"},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"text","text":"The Blackberry Technology Center is located at 316 Blackberry St., Harrisburg."},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"hard_break"},{"type":"text","text":"https://theburgnews.com/business/idea-factory-blackberry-technology-center-opens-downtown"},{"type":"hard_break"}]}]},"source":"The Burg:  BioHiTech Global is part of the tech boom in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania"}